@startuml 13_Multi_Env_Promotion
!theme plain
title 3D Data Quality Framework - Rule Promotion (Dev -> Prod)

skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor #ECEFF1
  BorderColor #90A4AE
  ArrowColor #546E7A
  StartColor #4CAF50
  EndColor #F44336
  DiamondBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
  DiamondBorderColor #F9A825
}

|#E3F2FD| DEV Environment |
|#FCE4EC| PRODUCTION Environment |
|#E8F5E9| Governance Gate |

start

|DEV Environment|
:Data Engineer creates DQ rule via Agent\n(status: DRAFT -> PENDING_APPROVAL -> ACTIVE);
note right
  DEPLOY_ENV = dev
  Catalog: lakehouse_dev
  Schema:  ds_tda_governance_lhdev
end note

:Rule executes in DEV via ANOMALY_DETECTION_JOB\nfor minimum 3 days of observed runs;

:Review DEV execution results:\n- False positive rate\n- Execution duration (avg, p95)\n- Violation trend (stable / noisy?)\n- Cost (DBU per run);

if (Rule passes DEV quality bar?) then (No)
  :Revise rule - adjust SQL,\nthreshold or exception config;
  note right: Loop until DEV results\nare stable and acceptable
else (Yes)
endif

:Submit promotion request to Production\n(logged in check_execution_log /\nanomaly_check_config with DEV summary);

|Governance Gate|
:Tech Lead + Data Governance review:\n- DEV execution results (3+ days)\n- SQL + trend score\n- Performance benchmarks\n- False positive analysis\n- Compliance / PII impact (GDPR, SOX)\n- Rule classification + priority;

if (Approved for Production?) then (No)
  |DEV Environment|
  :Receive revision feedback\nAdjust rule and re-test in DEV;
  stop
else (Yes)
endif

|PRODUCTION Environment|
:Rule promoted to PROD config\n(version_id incremented\nstatus: PENDING_APPROVAL);
note right
  DEPLOY_ENV = prod
  Catalog: lakehouse
  Schema:  ds_tda_governance_lh
end note

:Product Owner final sign-off\nin PRODUCTION environment;

:Rule set to is_active = true (ACTIVE)\nin anomaly_check_config;

:Added to production run schedule\n(priority P1/P2/P3 as classified);

:Monitoring and alerting configured:\n- Jira auto-ticket for P1/P2 violations\n- Email for P1 / P2 / P3\n- SLA tracking enabled;

' --- PROD Health Check (7-day observation) -----------------------------------
if (PROD health OK within 7 days?) then (Yes)

  |Governance Gate|
  :Promotion audit record created\n(both envs + approvers\n+ execution results documented);

  stop

else (No -- PROD regression detected)

  |PRODUCTION Environment|
  :Emergency disable rule in PROD\n(status -> DISABLED_EMERGENCY);
  note right
    SET is_active = false
    status = DISABLED_EMERGENCY
    rollback_reason + incident_id logged
  end note

  |Governance Gate|
  :Raise rollback incident ticket\nNotify owner + Tech Lead + DataOps;

  |PRODUCTION Environment|
  :Notify rule owner + PO\nwith PROD failure analysis\n(execution logs, violation sample, blast radius);

  |DEV Environment|
  :Investigate root cause in DEV\nApply fix to DEV rule version\n(version_id bump);

  :Re-enter DEV observation period\n(minimum 3 days from scratch);

  note right
    Rollback completes here.
    To re-promote: restart flow from
    "Submit promotion request to Production".
    Previous PROD version remains DISABLED_EMERGENCY
    until incident is formally closed.
  end note

  stop

endif

note right
  Promotion Metadata Tracked
  in anomaly_check_config (version_id):
  -------------------------
  - promoted_from_env (dev)
  - promoted_by (user + approver)
  - promotion_date
  - dev_execution_summary (JSON)
  - compliance_sign_off
  - effective_prod_date
end note

@enduml
